Laellanna/Daena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urasputyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rasputyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/15/01 6:12:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> The way that I like to do it is like Little Cherub said.<br>
First off I use both Naltron and Pinzarn (sp??).  Melee all get Naltron and everyone else gets Pinzarn.   I also always have my enchanter hotkeyed for a heal.  Now money items are rare in places like Karnors so I volunteer to ML.  I then ask if anyone minds if I keep the FS to offset Reagent cost.  I tried to keep at least 10 to 12 slots free for FS.  Now that would make me heavier but with a CHA buff would sell for 50 to 60 PP.  That would help quite a bit.  Now of course Seb is better but sometimes small items add up and help cover costs.   It is not to be greedy but I would be very broke without it.<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urasputyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rasputyn</A> at: 10/15/01 6:14:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umathii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/17/01 4:23:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> *pokes her head in*<br>
<br>
As a shaman generally I ask not to be symboled in a regular group.  I always have regen and my own HP buffs on me, HB is nice, and unless I or the puller do something stupid I dont need the extra hp.  <br>
A shaman should be able to control most of their own aggro, and the only time as a shaman I need extra HP is when I am trying to play crowd control.  Then I can get beat down pretty bad as roots break.  Generally speaking though most of the damage a good shaman takes is self-inflicted, with the occasional smack or 2 from a pissed off slowed mob.  Shamen generally have decent AC and HP and can take a couple smacks without trouble especially since the mobs smacking us are usually 70% slower than before <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Also, in any group I am in I try to make sure the clerics get their costs back.  I like grouping with clerics and I don't think anyone should leave a group with less cash than they started with.<br>
<br>
 <p>Mathi Bear<BR>
Luminary<BR>
